
[1]glair

   GLAIR, n. [Eng. clear, L. clarus, and with Eng. glare, and L. gloria;
   perhaps with L. glarea, gravel,or pieces of quartz.]

   1. The white of an egg. It is used as a varnish for preserving
   paintings.

   2. Any viscous transparent substance, resembling the white of an egg.

   3. A kind of halbert.

         GLAIR, v.t. To smear with the white of an egg; to varnish.
